ml\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sfv1665702708226.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/sfv1665702708226.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"sfv1665702708226\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      $itemcount\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"sfv1665702708226___itemcount_271093\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Return the number of items in a list.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"sfv1665702708226__topic_d85052e1_d85053e1_d85054e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sfv1665702708226__p_d85055e1_d85056e1_d85057e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$itemcount</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">List</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"sfv1665702708226__topic_d56432e1_d56433e1_d56434e1_d56435e1_d56436e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1216162e75\">\n                       \n Parameters\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"sfv1665702708226__table_d8891e1_d8892e1_d8893e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Parameters</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"sfv1665702708226__table_d8891e1_d8892e1_d8893e1__entry__1\">\n Parameter\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"sfv1665702708226__table_d8891e1_d8892e1_d8893e1__entry__2\">\n Data Type\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"sfv1665702708226__table_d8891e1_d8892e1_d8893e1__entry__3\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfv1665702708226__table_d8891e1_d8892e1_d8893e1__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">List</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfv1665702708226__table_d8891e1_d8892e1_d8893e1__entry__2\">\n String\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"sfv1665702708226__table_d8891e1_d8892e1_d8893e1__entry__3\">Name of the variable, parameter, or field\n                        containing the list. </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"sfv1665702708226__topic_d56437e1_d56438e1_d56439e1_d56440e1_d56441e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1216162e129\">\n                       \n Return Values\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sfv1665702708226__p_d85064e1_d85065e1_d85066e1\">Number of items in a list.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"sfv1665702708226__topic_d56442e1_d56443e1_d56444e1_d56445e1_d56446e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1216162e138\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sfv1665702708226__d5916e20\">Allowed in all component types.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"sfv1665702708226__topic_d56447e1_d56448e1_d56449e1_d56450e1_d56451e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1216162e148\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"sfv1665702708226__p_d85076e1_d85077e1_d85078e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$itemcount</span> function enables you to determine how many items are in a list before processing each item.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"sfv1665702708226__section_wqh_lx1_1cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1216162e160\">Example: Using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$itemcount</span></h2>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"sfv1665702708226__pre_vjr_lx1_1cc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$1 = 0\n$2 = $itemcount (\"$mylist$\")\nwhile $1 &lt;= $2\n $1 += 1\nendwhile</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cip1665702554022.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>List Handling in ProcScript</a><p>Uniface provides ProcScript instructions that enable you to build lists, retrieve items from lists, and sort lists based on various criteria.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gan1665702559756.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$idpart</a><p>Return the ID part of an associative list item.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ytj1665702559912.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$valuepart</a><p>Return the value part of an associative list item.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531957\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531957\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$itemcount Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 10, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 $itemcount Return the number of items in a list. $itemcount ( List ) Parameters Table 1. Parameters Parameter Data Type Description List String Name of the variable, parameter, or field containing the list. Return Values Number of items in a list. Use Allowed in all component types. Description The $itemcount function enables you to determine how many items are in a list before processing each item. Example: Using $itemcount $1 = 0 $2 = $itemcount (\"$mylist$\") while $1 <= $2 $1 += 1 endwhile Copy Related Links List Handling in ProcScript Uniface provides ProcScript instructions that enable you to build lists, retrieve items from lists, and sort lists based on various criteria. $idpart Return the ID part of an associative list item. $valuepart Return the value part of an associative list item. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}